The dataset shows clear imbalance across demographic groups, particularly in gender, race, and age categories, which directly impacts model fairness. The Logistic Regression model achieved good overall accuracy, but fairness analysis revealed disparities in precision and recall between groups, indicating biased predictions toward majority populations. Before mitigation, underrepresented groups had lower recall, meaning the model failed more often to correctly identify high-income individuals within those groups. After applying reweighting, fairness improved, especially for gender-based groups, as precision and recall became more balanced. However, this improvement came with a slight trade-off in accuracy, highlighting the ethical challenge of balancing model performance with fairness in real-world applications.
